tarter as an extra Maven dependency. The idea is to avoid unnecessary actions unless there’s solid evidence that an additional setup is needed. Also, I wonder if any generated scaffold could import classes that require optional dependencies, which could cause compile issues if they’re missing. For Spring Boot Actuator 3.0, many public classes reference these optional dependencies.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Investigating metric dependencies**\\n\\nI’m thinking about the potential issue if generated tests select `MetricsEndpoint` without including micrometer-core. This could lead to compile failures since constructor types like `MeterRegistry`, `MeterFilter`, and `Meter` would be missing. It seems we could still achieve meaningful coverage by avoiding optional integration classes or by adding the necessary dependencies. Should I set up micrometer-core since the starter-actuator uses it and metrics endpoints are so central? I’ll need to research the source dependencies to clarify this.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_PBRpbpDz1gX0gzn5dEqTw47p|fc_01804db6af1cad7c016a42596c8f048196b0965dbd1fc2f46d", "name": "bash", "arguments": {"command": "tmp=$(mktemp -d)\npython3 - <<'PY' \"$tmp\"\nimport urllib.request, pathlib, sys, zipfile, re\nbase='https://repo1.maven.org/maven2/org/springframework/boot/spring-boot-actuator/3.0.0/'\nfor fn in ['spring-boot-actuator-3.0.0-sources.jar']:\n p=pathlib.Path(sys.argv[1])/fn\n p.write_bytes(urllib.request.urlopen(base+fn, timeout=30).read())\nwith zipfile.ZipFile(pathlib.Path(sys.argv[1])/'spring-boot-actuator-3.0.0-sources.jar') as z:\n    names=z.namelist()\n    for pat in ['HttpTrace', 'HttpExchange', 'MetricsEndpoint.java','EnvironmentEndpoint.java','HealthEndpoint.java']:\n        print('\\nPAT', pat)\n        for n in names:\n            if pat in n:\n                print(n)\n                txt=z.read(n).decode('utf-8', 'ignore')\n                print('\\n'.join(txt.splitlines()[:60]))\n                break\nPY", "timeout": 60}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 785, "output": 1070, "cacheRead": 26112, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 27967, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1782733150405, "responseId": "resp_01804db6af1cad7c016a42595ef02081968cf6c4a565a8e5cc"}, "toolResults": [{"role": "toolResult", "toolCallId": "call_PBRpbpDz1gX0gzn5dEqTw47p|fc_01804db6af1cad7c016a42596c8f048196b0965dbd1fc2f46d", "toolName": "bash", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "\nPAT HttpTrace\n\nPAT HttpExchange\norg/springframework/boot/actuate/web/exchanges/servlet/HttpExchangesFilter.java\n/*\n * Copyright 2012-2022 the original author or authors.\n *\n * Licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0 (the \"License\");\n * you may not use this file except in compliance with the License.\n * You may obtain a copy of the License at\n *\n *      https://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0\n *\n * Unless required by applicable law or agreed to in writing, software\n * distributed under the License is distributed on an \"AS IS\" BASIS,\n * WITHOUT WARRANTIES OR CONDITIONS OF ANY KIND, either express or implied.\n * See the License for the specific language governing permissions and\n * limitations under the License.\n */\n\npackage org.springframework.boot.actuate.web.exchanges.servlet;\n\nimport java.io.IOException;\nimport java.net.URI;\nimport java.net.URISyntaxException;\nimport java.util.Set;\n\nimport jakarta.servlet.Filter;\nimport jakarta.servlet.FilterChain;\nimport jakarta.servlet.ServletException;\nimport jakarta.servlet.http.HttpServletRequest;\nimport jakarta.servlet.http.HttpServletResponse;\nimport jakarta.servlet.http.HttpSession;\n\nimport org.springframework.boot.actuate.web.exchanges.HttpExchange;\nimport org.springframework.boot.actuate.web.exchanges.HttpExchangeRepository;\nimport org.springframework.boot.actuate.web.exchange