solves with Spring Boot and Spring Framework core/context, and meaningful actuator coverage is reachable by directly exercising core endpoints and repositories. The reported javac failure is caused by Spring Boot 2.6-era API usage against 3.0.0, not by missing Docker, dependency, or environment setup.\",\n  \"deterministic_setup\": [],\n  \"agent_guidance\": \"No environment variables or system properties are required. Generated tests should use Spring Boot 3.0 actuator APIs, such as HTTP exchanges instead of the removed HttpTrace APIs, and should instantiate core actuator endpoints directly rather than requiring a full web application.\",\n  \"risks\": [\n    \"The actuator jar contains optional integration classes for Micrometer, servlet/reactive web stacks, and external systems such as Redis, MongoDB, RabbitMQ, and Elasticsearch. Importing those classes without their optional dependencies can cause javac failures, but they are not required for meaningful core coverage.\"\n  ]\n}", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_01804db6af1cad7c016a425983be6c8196a82d309152a17fa7\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 1579, "output": 742, "cacheRead": 29696, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 32017, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "stop", "timestamp": 1782733177761, "responseId": "resp_01804db6af1cad7c016a42597a7f3481968758d01645f41838"}, "toolResults": []}
